com.ibm.ccl.soa.deploy.core.validator.resolution.param
Interface IDeployResolutionParameter

All Known Subinterfaces:
IDeployResolutionObjectAttributeParameter
All Known Implementing Classes:
DeployResolutionObjectAttributeParameter, DeployResolutionParameter
public interface IDeployResolutionParameter

The parameter bound to a parameterized deploy resolution instance.

The parameter is bound to a parameterized deploy resolution.

See Also:
IDeployParameterizedResolution, IDeployParameterizedResolution.getParameters()

validate

IStatus validate()
Validates the value of the parameter.

The parameter is bound to a resolution (getResolution()) which is bound to a status IDeployResolution.getDeployStatus()) which is bound to an object (IDeployStatus.getDeployObject()) contained in a topology (DeployModelObject.getTopology()).

The value is validated in the context of the resolution object, and topology.

Returns:
the status of validating the proposed value (never null).

getValidValueDescriptors

java.util.List<IDeployResolutionParameterValueDescriptor> getValidValueDescriptors()
Returns a list of valid value descritors for the parameter.

The list contains the values and their descriptions. The list may not be exclusive (use isValidValueListExclusive()) to determine if other values are permitted.

Returns:
a list of valid values and their descriptions (never null).

isValidValueListExclusive

boolean isValidValueListExclusive()
Check if other values in addition to the ones return by getValidValueDescriptors() are allowed.

Returns:
true if users can set to additional values, false if only the valid values are valid choices.
